    public interface ITupR
    Author:
    picatrix1899 This interface represents a readonly version of a unspecialized n-dimensional immutable tuple.

    • Method Detail

      • getUni

        double getUni(int index)
        Returns the value from the tuple at the given index. This is a generalized fuction and is as such available in all derivations of tuples.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the value to return.
        Returns:
        The value from the tuple at the given index.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException - Thrown when the given index is smaller than 0 or greater than the tuples' size - 1.

      • getDimensions

        int getDimensions()
        Returns the dimension or value count of the tuple. This is often used together with the getUni(int) function.
        Returns:
        The dimension or value count of the tuple.

      • isFinite

        boolean isFinite()
        Returns true if all values of the tuple are finite values.
        Returns:
        True if all values of the tuple are finite values.
